      "titleEn": "Friends (1)",
      "titleCn": "",
      "audioSrc": "./follow-reading/junior/011.m4a",
      "transcriptEn": "Friends are different things to different people. To my little sister, a friend is someone who likes to swim and ride bikes. My mom's idea of a friend is someone like Mrs. Smith who walks and talks with her every morning. My dad's friends are neighbors who help him with the work like building shelves and planting trees.",
      "transcriptCn": "6．朋友(1)\n\n对于不同的人(people)，朋友(friend)意味着不同的(different)内容。对于我的小妹妹(little sister)来说，朋友是喜欢(like)游泳和骑自行车(ride bikes)的某个人(someone)。我妈妈的想法(idea)是朋友像(like)史密斯夫人一样可以每天早上陪她散步(walk)并交谈(talk)。我爸爸的朋友是帮他搭建架子(build shelves)、种树(plant trees)或做其他活的邻居们(neighbors)。",
      "sentences": [
        "Friends are different things to different people.",
        "To my little sister, a friend is someone who likes to swim and ride bikes.",
        "My mom's idea of a friend is someone like Mrs.",
        "Smith who walks and talks with her every morning.",
        "My dad's friends are neighbors who help him with the work like building shelves and planting trees."
      ]
